Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}. In a #medium bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} with @white wine vinegar{4%tsp}. Add @shredded carrots{4%ounce} to bowl and toss to coat, then set aside.

Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into 1/2-inch pieces and place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until potatoes are easily pierced by a knife, about ~{15%minutes}. Scoop out and reserve ¼ cup cooking water (½ cup for 4 servings), then drain potatoes and return to #pot.

Meanwhile, rub @pork chops{12%ounce} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}. Season all over with plenty of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside ¼ tsp @smoky cinnamon paprika spice{1%tablespoon} (½ tsp for 4 servings) in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, then rub pork all over with remaining spice. Place pork on a #baking sheet{} and roast until cooked through, ~{13-15%minutes}. Let rest ~{5%minutes} after removing from oven.

Meanwhile, quarter, core, and thinly slice @apple{1}. Add to bowl with carrots and toss to combine. Stir in half the scallions. Season with salt and pepper.

To bowl with reserved spice, add @cherry jam{3%tablespoon} and @white wine vinegar{½%tsp}.

  (For 4 servings, also add 1 tsp water.) Stir to combine. Microwave until warm, about ~{45%seconds}. Add @butter{1%TBSP} and stir until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Mash drained potatoes in pot with a #potato masher{} or fork until smooth. Stir in @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, remaining scallions, reserved cooking water, and @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Season with salt and pepper.

Divide pork, mashed potatoes, and slaw between plates. Top pork with sauce.